## Conventions

### Package Scripts

| Command | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| `pnpm install` | Install all workspace dependencies |
| `pnpm test` | Run all tests (Turbo) |
| `pnpm build` | Build all packages |
| `pnpm dev` | Dev mode (all apps) |
| `pnpm lint` | Lint all packages |
| `pnpm type-check` | Type-check all packages |
| `pnpm db:generate` | Generate Drizzle migrations |
| `pnpm db:migrate` | Run Drizzle migrations |
| `pnpm db:seed` | Seed database |
| `pnpm docker:up` | Start Docker services |

### Package Dependencies

- **Internal packages**: use `workspace:*` (e.g., `"@printflow/common": "workspace:*"`)
- **vitest config**: every package needs `vitest.config.ts` with `passWithNoTests: true`
- **tsconfig**: extends `@printflow/tsconfig/tsconfig.json`

### API Conventions

- All routers return `ApiResponse<T>` via `successResponse()` / `errorResponse()`
- Auth middleware sets `request.userId`, `request.userName`, `request.roles`
- Zod validation on all request bodies and params
- Error codes: `INVALID_CREDENTIALS`, `USERNAME_EXISTS`, `TOTP_REQUIRED`, etc.

### Naming Conventions

- Database tables: `snake_case` (e.g., `user_name`, `date_created`)
- TypeScript: `camelCase` for vars/funcs, `PascalCase` for types/classes
- Files: `kebab-case.ts`
- API routes: `kebab-case.ts` (e.g., `printers.ts` not `printersRouter.ts`)

### Testing

- Test files: `*.test.ts` next to source
- Run tests: `pnpm test` (root) or `pnpm test` (per package)
- vitest globals: `true` (no import needed)
